title: Mount Warning-Wollumbin track closure plans sparks outrage among hikers
description: The Mount Warning-Wollumbin hiking trail in the Tweed Shire, in far north New South Wales, will soon no longer be accessible to visitors after concerns expressed by traditional custodians.

title: Single-engine plane crashes into New Hampshire apartment building killing EVERYONE on board
description: A single-engine plane that crashed into a New Hampshire apartment building has killed everyone on board.

title: Brisbane family gets terrifying anonymous note threatening to kill their dogs with poisoned treats
description: A Brisbane family with two large rescue dogs have received a menacing letter from an anonymous neighbour threatening to poison their pets with chocolate if they do not stop barking.

title: Recycling centre worker in Findon, Adelaide allegedly attacked after refusing to count containers
description: Police are on the hunt for a man who allegedly attacked a recycling worker in a 'senseless' act in Findon, Adelaide on Thursday.

title: Bidens excruciating pause when asked if Jill wants him to run again in 2024 before dodging question
description: President Joe Biden appeared to completely lose focus during an interview. Asked what his wife Dr. Jill Biden think about him possibly running 2024, the president seemed to zone out.

title: MPs demand probe into China's plans to build 'super-embassy' opposite the Tower of London
description: MPs, members of the House of Lords and stakeholders have demanded a probe into the country's plans to convert the old Royal Mint into a 'super-embassy'.

title: Suella Braverman and Kemi Badenoch face pressure to stand aside to avoid fracturing the Tory Right
description: Suella Braverman and Kemi Badenoch were under pressure last night to step aside to avoid splitting the Tory Right. MPs warned they could dent the chances of Boris Johnson.

title: Soaring house prices and frozen allowances force inheritance tax up to record £7BILLION
description: Britons are on track to pay a record £7billion in inheritance tax this year as a result of frozen allowances and soaring house prices, experts have warned.

title: Nearly two in five mortgages will not end until 2052: Homeowners turn to ultra-long loans
description: Almost two in five new mortgages are being taken out for 30 years or more as homeowners turn to ultra-long deals to keep down monthly repayments.

title: Mother of boy who saved sister's life by diving in front of SUV begs driver to come forward
description: Tyler Phillips, of Medford, New York, was sent flying when he was hit by a gray SUV, just one day after celebrating his birthday, as he rushed in to save his 14-year-old sister, Krystal Randolph, on October 12.

title: Armed police stormed easyJet passenger plane at Stansted after passengers sent bomb threat message
description: Armed police stormed an easyJet plane at Stansted airport after passengers were sent a terrifying AirDrop message that said 'I have a bomb'.

title: Defence spending needs to be squeezed to balance the books, Jeremy Hunt will warn new prime minister
description: Jeremy Hunt is to warn Britain's new prime minister that they need to squeeze defence spending and axe the prison-building programme within days to help balance the books.

title: Dr Az Hakeem says parents claimed their kids were trans at NHS Tavistock 'transing factory' clinic
description: Dr Az Hakeem worked at the NHS clinic for 12 years until 2012 and said he expressed concerns the procedures followed by staff 'were mad', describing Tavistock as a 'transing factory'.

title: Ivanka Trump shows off huge dark ROOTS as she teaches horse-riding Jared Kusher $24m mansion move
description: Exclusive DailyMail.com photos shows Ivanka Trump spending part of her weekend earlier this month at a horse riding lesson for her daughter, Arabella, 11, but with dark roots showing through.

title: Rio Madeira loses power and drifts off Narooma, NSW coast as rescue boats are deployed
description: A rescue mission is underway to save the Rio Madeira cargo ship which has drifted out to sea with around 10,000 containers on board, after it lost power about 80km off the coast of Narooma, NSW.

title: Vladimir Putin's dambusters 'threaten to unleash catastrophic flood in new scare tactic Kyiv warns
description: Russia has mined a huge hydroelectric dam in southern Ukraine in a plot to unleash a devastating flood, after Moscow's failed 'nuclear blackmail', officials in Kyiv have warned.

title: Washington town forced to removed Karen-themed Halloween display after resident accused resemblance
description: Maricela Sanchez claimed the scarecrow donning a 'Can I speak to the manager' shirt and had shoulder-length black hair resembled her.

title: King Charles 'is planning Royal Family's biggest ever global tour to kick off his reign'
description: The King will visit Australia, New Zealand and several Commonwealth countries in the Caribbean. The  monarch is reported to be planning various domestic and foreign trips by himself

title: Federal appeals court HALTS Biden's student loan forgiveness program
description: A federal appeals court in Missouri has temporarily blocked the Biden administration's forgiveness of student loan debt, saying they need more time to consider a Republican challenge.
